<section class="hero">
  <h1>A private group chat<br />for the people you trust.</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Eleven Messenger keeps family and close friends in one place — end-to-end
    encrypted, so the server only ever sees ciphertext and your conversations
    stay yours. No accounts, no passwords, no ads, no tracking. Just a secret
    invite link.
  </p>
  <div class="cta">
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#get">Get Eleven Messenger</a>
    <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/privacy/">How your privacy works</a>
  </div>
  <p class="fine">
    Invite-only — there's no public sign-up. Someone already in a chat sends you
    a link.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="features" aria-label="What makes Eleven Messenger different">
  <div class="feature">
    <h3>End-to-end encrypted</h3>
    <p>
      Every message is encrypted in your browser before it leaves your device.
      The server stores and relays only ciphertext it can't open — even a stolen
      database exposes no message content.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="feature">
    <h3>Safe for kids by default</h3>
    <p>
      Built for families. It defaults to the safest option and stays small and
      quiet — no ads, no algorithms, no strangers, no feed to get lost in.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="feature">
    <h3>No logins, no passwords</h3>
    <p>
      You join with a one-time secret link, and your own device holds the keys.
      Nothing to remember, nothing to phish, nothing to leak.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="feature">
    <h3>Everywhere you are</h3>
    <p>
      A native app on Mac and iPhone, or just open your invite link in any
      browser. The same chats and the same keys, wherever you sign in.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

